<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fate2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fate,</orth> vb., to ordain, to destine: <cit><quote>as it hath --d her to be my motive,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 4, 20</bibl></cit>. Part. <emph>--ed</emph> == doomed, decreed by destiny: <emph>one midnight --ed to the purpose,</emph> Tp. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. aww 4.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.276" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 276</bibl>.
